title: For Sale:  Beretta 71
postcontent:
The Beretta 71 was never imported into the United States in great numbers, particularly with a 3.5-inch barrel (which was unfortunately banned from further importation by the Gun Control Act of 1968), hence the current, permanently attached faux suppressor which stretches the barrel length out to a full 9 inches.

This is a non suppressor Beretta 71 that was imported this summer. No need for any ATF paperwork since there is only a fake suppressor (non removable) on it.

More History:

 One of the most interesting references to the Mossad’s choice of the Beretta .22 is contained in a thesis on counter-terrorism submitted in April 1995 to the Marine Corps Command and Staff College, written by Alexander B. Calahan. It’s on the web.

Calahan’s thesis documents the Mossad assassination teams organized immediately after the terrorist massacre of 11 Israeli athletes at the Munich Olympic Games in September 1972. In retaliation, the Mossad teams were given a specific list of terrorist targets to eliminate. Throughout the thesis there are continual references to Beretta .22’

title: For Sale/Trade:  Remington R-25 / R25, 308 Win, 20in Barrel, New In Case NEVER SHOOT AR-10
postcontent:
Remington R-25 / R25, 308 Win, 20in Barrel, New In Case NEVER SHOOT AR-10

The Remington® R-25 Semi-Auto Rifle is built on the proven AR-10 platform, using the direct-impingement gas system, where gas is ported down a tube into the action to cycle the rotary bolt locking mechanism. The lack of an operating rod and piston allows the barrel to be free-floated, greatly improving inherent accuracy. Movement of the bolt carrier in-line with the bore, and the recoil spring inside the stock reduces recoil and muzzle jump considerably, allowing for rapid follow up shots at multiple targets or running game. The Model R-25's operation controls, including the bolt hold open/release, mag release, and forward assist, are the same as those of AR semi-automatic rifles. The Remington R-25 has a 20" fluted barrel that reduces weight and enhances heat dissipation. Both upper and lower are machined from rugged aluminum forgings, and a machined aluminum fore-end tube surrounds the free-floated barrel. A receiver-length Picatinny rail allows the attachment of AR tactical sights, or hunting scopes. A crisp, single-stage trigger comes from the factory set at 4-1/2 to 5 lbs. The Remington R-25 Semi-Auto Rifle comes with a 4-round magazine, and is compatible with aftermarket DPMS 308 Win-type magazines of greater capacity. Includes front and rear sling swivels. Made in USA.

The Firestar pistol M-45, was designed and manufactured by the Spanish company Star Bonifacio Echeverria SA.

All Firestars are compact, steel-framed semi-automatic pistols. Firestar pistols are recoil operated, with Browning cam locking and short barrel recoil. Firestar pistols are claimed to be ones of the smallest guns in their respective calibers, but, obviously not the lightest ones. postcontent: This Colt 1st Generation SAA was manufactured around 1901 and originally chambered in 38-40. Prior to WWII it was sent back to Colt and converted to fire 38 Spcl which was very popular at the time. The conversion is still 1st Generation as it was done in the late 1930's prior to the start of WWII. This particular revolver has an interesting family history, but I am selling it due to some urgent financial needs. The condition of this Colt is very good to excellent and it should be both a fantastic shooter as well as fine collectible at a reasonable price due to the conversion. This revolver has a 5 1/2" barrel and the bore looks great. Nice Colts like this are getting very hard to find so don't miss out. As with all older firearms this revolver must be checked out by a competent gunsmith prior to firing it. Buyer to pay actual shipping and provide copy of FFL.
